                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cmpl-511" class="program-course-title">
              CMPL 511 Social Diversity and Law (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-21028" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Law (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/627">Faculty of Law</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Comparative Law              : The interaction of law and cultural diversity. Through the use of a number of case studies, we will examine: 1. The empirical effect of cultural diversity on legal systems. 2. Institutional structures to accommodate diversity. 3. Theoretical perspectives.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              This course is not scheduled for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

