      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business Law 1              : Federal bankruptcy law, including bankruptcy petitions, an individual's rights to a discharge, the nature of claims provable in bankruptcy, the rejection and assumption of executory contracts, the stay of proceedings and the avoidance powers of trustees and receiverships and workouts as alternatives to bankruptcy proceedings. Students may not take both this course and either Bankruptcy and Insolvency or Protection and Enforcement of Creditors' Rights.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

