              <p>* With the approval of the Associate Dean Academic, in consultation with the Faculty Supervisors, on a case-by-case basis.</p>
      
                <h4>Elective Courses</h4>

    
              <p>37-43 credits.</p>
<p>Students must take 37 to 43 other elective courses offered within the Faculty or approved as credit equivalences in order to complete the 105-credit degree requirement.</p>
    
      
      
                <h4>Minimum Writing Requirement </h4>

    
              <p>All students are required to submit at least one research paper. This requirement may be satisfied by: </p>
<p>a) writing an essay in a course in which the essay constitutes no less than 75% of the final grade; </p>
<p>b) writing a term essay under independent supervision, for credit, within the Faculty of Law; </p>
<p>c) writing an article, note, or comment of equivalent substance that is published or accepted for publication in the McGill Law Journal and approved by the Faculty Adviser to that publication. </p>
<p>Papers written jointly do not satisfy this requirement.</p>
    
      
      
            </div>

    
  
